      "writtenOn": "2018-04-16T11:12:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The above algorithm to compute the valid HVA range for qemu_ram_load() is straightforward, but I have an idea to simplify it. Could you split this CL and create a separate one for hax-all.c? That way I could replace this algorithm and test it against the rest of this CL that enables the bulk loading API.\n\nHere\u0027s a sketch of the new algorithm (I actually discussed this idea briefly with Haitao):\n\n1. Find the hax_memslot (slot) containing the faulting GPA. There must be one (and only one).\n2. Convert the faulting GPA to HVA (fault_hva) using mapping info from |slot|.\n3. Compute the upper and lower bounds of the HVA range of the 2MB chunk containing |fault_hva|. Right now this is not trivial/possible, but I\u0027ll make a HAXM-side patch to redefine chunk boundaries based on absolute HVAs rather than RAM block boundaries, so this computation will be as easy as rounding |fault_hva| down and up to the nearest 2MB boundaries.\n4. Compute the intersection of a) the HVA range obtained from step 3, and b) the HVA range covered by |slot|.\n\nThe new algorithm only scans the memslot array once, and doesn\u0027t call hax_gpa2hva() at all.",
      "revId": "39e81b009135c5d16f684be3fae0dee3182c8ebd",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
